Package de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.api

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IGarmentAPI
    This interface defines all the available methods for the IPC
    IGarmentCallback
    This Interface defines the method available for callback objects
    IGarmentDriver
    This interface defines the methods every driver has to provide
    ISensorDriver  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActivityChangedCallback
    This Callback object is returned when the Activity of the User has changed and the app has registered itself for being called back once this event happens
    APIFunctions
    This class provides of all the available function that can be called from any application that has bound its connection to the service.
    APIFunctionsAsync
    Basically the same as APIFunctions with the only difference that these functions will be executed asynchronously.
    AsyncResultObject
    This class represents a result object from an asynchronous API function call.
    BaseCallbackObject
    BaseCallbackObject class represents the type of objects that are send back by callback from the garment OS service.
    CallbackFlags
    As provided by the APIFunctions.registerCallback(IGarmentCallback, int) the developer has the ability to register for several different events that are recognized during the runtime of the GarmentOS Service.
    CallbackHandler
    This class is being used as callback Handler for the Garment OS Service.
    CallBackObject
    Callback object that is actually used to be sent back.
    IGarmentAPI.Stub
    Local-side IPC implementation stub class.
    IGarmentCallback.Stub
    Local-side IPC implementation stub class.
    IGarmentDriver.Stub
    Local-side IPC implementation stub class.
    ISensorDriver.Stub
    Local-side IPC implementation stub class.
    PSensor
    Sensor object that can be used on the client side
    PSensorData
    Parcelable Sensor Data object.
    ValueChangedCallback
    Callback object that is returned when a sensor has gotten new values
